tutory or other requirement of confidentiality.</p><p>If you have received this message in error, please call 1300 362 072 to inform the sender so that future errors can be avoided.</p><p>---------------------------------------------------------------------</p><p><br /></p><p>Â </p><p><br /></p><p>Â </p><p><br /></p><p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------</p><p>This email, and any attachments, may be confidential and also privileged. If you are not the intended recipient, please notify the sender and delete all copies of this transmission along with any attachments immediately. You should not copy or use it for any purpose, nor disclose its contents to any other person.</p><p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------</p><p><br /></p><p>Â 2 Attachments</p><p>Â  â€¢Â  Scanned by Gmail</p><p><br /></p><p>Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p>Thu, Sep 20, 2012, 6:19â€¯PM</p><p>to Human</p><p><br /></p><p>The tribunal decision was the only decision that was any good that entire experience, if you read the events. I will be filling this out and get back with you.</p><p>...</p><p><br /></p><p>[Message clipped]Â  View entire message</p><p><br /></p><p>Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p>Sun, Sep 30, 2012, 3:24â€¯PM</p><p>to Human</p><p><br /></p><p>Dear Jennifer,</p><p><br /></p><p>I have not forgotten about this and I will do it. But right now I am getting very popular (because of my work on these issues) and I will wait for my reputation to landslide before I submit this paperwork. I have dealt with complaint services throughout the mental health systems and they do not listen nor care.</p><p><br /></p><p>The mental health systems of Australia look at me as insane for my philosophical investments. But I have done a great deal of work that is being discovered by many people. I also have been presented opportunities that might end up with me tackling these subjects in mainstream media.</p><p><br /></p><p>The world is discovering the things that I have done. The course, My Reflected Death clearly demonstrates the shortcomings and failures of our current mental health services. The entire thing (over 850 minutes) points directly at our mental health systems and everything I explain in it is then demonstrated to be accurate by the way that the one in Canberra treated me, which was the finale to this course. One day you will listen instead of brushing me off as dust on your shoulders.</p><p><br /></p><p>I am not going anywhere. Your systems think that if they brush me off that I will one day give up. Nothing is further from the truth. I will fight against your systems with every breath that I have within me and will not stop until they recognise the faults and create methods to resolve them. These systems are the oppressors of society and the ever sharpening power behind my words will one day change them, or I will die trying to do it.</p><p><br /></p><p>This is my life and being ignored when I have extremely important things to say about it will have its repercussions. Unthinking systems like our mental health services are practically demonstrated for their absurdity in all of my philosophy courses.</p><p><br /></p><p>Look forward to my submission. It will be in your hands once the world realises what I have done.</p><p><br /></p><p>Sincerely,</p><p><br /></p><p>Wendell Charles NeSmith (remember the name, for you will hear it for the rest of your life)</p><p>...</p><p><br /></p><p>[Message clipped]Â  View entire message</p><p>Displaying weddingNight.jpg. ACT</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p>Attachment KABUEnterTheZohar.png added.Conversation opened. 1 read message.</p><p><br /></p><p>Skip to content</p><p>Using Gmail with screen readers</p><p>"ACT HUMAN RIGHTS"Â </p><p>193 of 195</p><p>Re: Your health services enquiry</p><p><br /></p><p>Wendell Charles NeSmith <wendell@nesmith.net></p><p>Mon, Jan 28, 2013, 10:18â€¯PM</p